com.nokia.dempsy.router
Interface RoutingStrategy.Outbound.Coordinator

Enclosing interface:
RoutingStrategy.Outbound
public static interface RoutingStrategy.Outbound.Coordinator

Each node can have many Outbound instances and those Outbound cluster references can come and go. In order to tell Dempsy about what's going on in the cluster the Outbound should be updating the state of the OutboundCoordinator.

Implementors of the RoutingStrategy do not need to implement this interface. There is only one implementation and that instance will be supplied by the framework.

registers the outbound with the Coordinator and provide what types the destination cluster can handle. Note that the Outbound is allowed to call registerOutbound more than once, without calling unregisterOutbound first but the results should be the same.
